{
  "name": "oncocare",
  "version": "3.0",
  "description": "OncoCare Therapeutics ONC-441 Phase III clinical trial dataset \u2014 targeted therapy for advanced non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC), 2,400 patients across 12 international trial sites, 24-month enrollment window. Hidden story: SITE-07 (Sao Paulo, Brazil) has 34% protocol deviation rate (vs 8% system avg), administered 85% of protocol dose due to undocumented tolerability concerns, producing 31% response rate (vs 54% at other sites) \u2014 dragging trial-wide response from 54% down to 49.8%, just below FDA accelerated approval threshold.",
  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "RealityDB Atelier Module 6 (OncoCare) \u2014 VP of Clinical Operations investigation of DSMB-flagged site outlier before FDA advisory meeting; HireSQL biotech/clinical-trial assessments; SimLab efficacy analytics scenarios",
    "version": "1.0",
    "created": "2026-05-17",
    "updated": "2026-05-17",
    "author": "Eddy Mkwambe / Mpingo Systems",
    "scale_target": "30,000 rows across 24-month enrollment window May 2024 - May 2026 (smaller than other packs \u2014 clinical trials run smaller)",
    "company": {
      "name": "OncoCare Therapeutics",
      "stage": "Pre-NDA submission, Phase III ongoing",
      "trial_id": "ONC-441-P3-001",
      "drug": "ONC-441 targeted therapy",
      "indication": "Advanced non-small cell lung cancer (NSCLC)",
      "patients_enrolled": 2400,
      "sites": 12,
      "trigger_event": "DSMB interim analysis flagged one treatment arm underperforming; overall response rate 49.8% just below FDA accelerated-approval threshold of 50%; CMO needs full root-cause investigation before FDA advisory meeting in 6 weeks"
    },
    "story": {
      "summary": "Trial Site 7 (Sao Paulo, Brazil) has 34% protocol deviation rate vs 8% system-wide. Type: dose modification \u2014 administering 85% of protocol 400mg dose. Reason: site investigators downgraded doses due to tolerability concerns but never escalated to sponsor. Site 7 response rate is 31% vs 54% at other sites. Adverse event severity at Site 7 is LOWER (consistent with underdosing \u2014 less drug, fewer side effects, less efficacy). Site 7 represents 18% of enrolled patients; including them drags overall response rate from 54.1% to 49.8%.",
      "smoking_gun": "SITE-07 dose 85% of protocol + 34% deviation rate + 31% response (vs 54%) + MILDER adverse events (severity grades 1-2 at 85% vs 70% elsewhere) all visible together when stratified by site_code. The milder AEs are the epistemic twist \u2014 students must recognize this means underdosing, not healthier patients.",
      "visibility_tiers": [
        "Surface (Ex 1-3): Trial portfolio understanding; overall response rate 49.8% vs FDA 50% threshold; response by site reveals SITE-07 outlier",
        "Investigation (Ex 4-6): Protocol deviations by site concentration; deviation type at SITE-07 (dose_modification dominant); dose adherence at SITE-07 = 85% of protocol",
        "Root cause (Ex 7-10): Adverse event severity at SITE-07 (milder than elsewhere); smoking gun \u2014 underdosing explains both lower AEs AND lower response; quantify exclusion impact (49.8% -> 54.1% if SITE-07 excluded); recommend scenario A (exclude) or B (remediate)"
      ],
      "enforcement": "Baseline distributions are written with UNIFORM behavior across all 12 sites. The SITE-07 underdosing story (34% deviation, 85% dose, 31% response, milder AEs, more for_cause monitoring visits) is enforced post-generation by scripts/enforce-oncocare-story.mjs (Stage 7). Filter must use sites.site_code='SITE-07' (bounded to 12 declared values) because the engine generates ~6 site rows per declared site_code. T0-T8 transformations + key interim_analyses.overall_response_rate set to exactly 0.498."
    },
    "exceptions": [
      {
        "rule": "trials count fixed 1, sites 12, treatment_arms 2",
        "actual": "~75-125 rows per root at 30K scale (engine sizes by cascade math)",
        "reason": "Engine has no per-table row-count override. Story-critical filtering uses sites.site_code='SITE-07' (bounded to 12 declared values), trials.trial_id (single value), treatment_arms.arm_code (bounded to 2 values).",
        "approved_by": "Eddy Mkwambe",
        "date": "2026-05-17"
      },
      {
        "rule": "Lesson 19 applied: created_at dropped from 8 event tables",
        "actual": "created_at present only on entity tables (trials, sites, treatment_arms, patients); dropped from event tables (visits, adverse_events, lab_results, protocol_deviations, dropout_events, response_assessments, site_monitoring_visits, interim_analyses)",
        "reason": "Each event table has ONE explicit temporal anchor (visits.scheduled_date, adverse_events.onset_date, lab_results.collection_date, protocol_deviations.detected_date, dropout_events.dropout_date, response_assessments.assessment_date, site_monitoring_visits.visit_date, interim_analyses.analysis_date). Adding created_at would produce 17% temporally broken rows per Lesson 16 evidence from TowerNet/ClearBank. Patients keeps created_at because enrollment_date is enrollment intent, not record creation time \u2014 they can legitimately differ.",
        "approved_by": "Eddy Mkwambe",
        "date": "2026-05-17"
      },
      {
        "rule": "Lesson 3 applied: adverse_events.action_taken 'none' value replaced",
        "actual": "Replaced 'none' enum value with explicit values ['observed', 'dose_reduction', 'dose_delay', 'discontinuation', 'hospitalization'] where 'observed' replaces 'none' semantically (action: clinical observation, no intervention)",
        "reason": "Per Lesson 3, 'none' as enum value flags as placeholder in assess. 'observed' is semantically correct for the underlying meaning (no intervention but ongoing clinical observation)."
      },
      {
        "rule": "Scale confidence target HIGH",
        "actual": "Expected LOW at 30K scale due to small interim_analyses (3 rows intent, will limit confidence per Lesson 18)",
        "reason": "interim_analyses is intentionally tiny (3 interim analyses per trial). Multiple small root-side tables limit cardinality variance metric. Per Lesson 18, more small roots can lower scale confidence. Accepting LOW for v1.0 baseline."
      },
      {
        "rule": "Distribution diversity 100",
        "actual": "Expected ~85-92",
        "reason": "Multiple inherent skewed ratios: severity_grade weighted toward grades 1-2 (real clinical reality), visit_status 82% completed, monitor visit_type 65% routine. Domain reality per Lesson 19 \u2014 documentation territory."
      }
    ],
    "open_questions": [
      "interim_analyses cardinality: spec asks for ~3 rows; engine will produce more. Enforcer targets the LATEST analysis for the 0.498 value.",
      "Boolean fields modeled as 'false'/'true' string enums (matches prior packs).",
      "Site name and country are aligned by position in spec \u2014 pack uses independent enums; enforcer can validate or rely on the position alignment after data load.",
      "ECOG performance status values 0/1/2 modeled as string enum (matches spec format)."
    ],
    "citations": [
